# User & admin guide sync (mandatory)

Customer and admin documentation must stay aligned with the live UI. The app enforces this at build/import time.

## Source of truth

| Area | Registry (routes, labels, locations) | Content (prose, policies) |
|------|--------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Customer UI | `src/lib/documentation/customer-ui-surfaces.ts` | `src/lib/user-documentation.ts` тЖТ `CUSTOMER_DOCUMENTATION_CONTENT_RAW` |
| Customer sidebar | `CUSTOMER_SIDEBAR_NAV_LINKS` in same file тАФ consumed by `dashboard-nav.tsx` | тАФ |
| Admin UI | `src/lib/documentation/admin-ui-surfaces.ts` | `src/lib/admin-documentation.ts` тЖТ `ADMIN_DOCUMENTATION_CONTENT_RAW` |
| Admin sidebar | `ADMIN_SIDEBAR_NAV_LINKS` in same file тАФ consumed by `admin-nav.tsx` | тАФ |

Built guide sections merge registry metadata (title, category, **location**) with content via `src/lib/documentation/sync-documentation.ts`.

## When you change customer or admin UI

1. **New sidebar page or renamed nav link** тАФ update `CUSTOMER_SIDEBAR_NAV_LINKS` or `ADMIN_SIDEBAR_NAV_LINKS` (href, label, docId, navSection). Add matching `docId` surface overrides if the guide title differs from the nav label.
2. **New header control, modal, tab, or public page** тАФ add a `UiSurfaceDefinition` entry in the appropriate `*-ui-surfaces.ts` file (id, route, location, category).
3. **Add guide content** тАФ add a section to `CUSTOMER_DOCUMENTATION_CONTENT_RAW` or `ADMIN_DOCUMENTATION_CONTENT_RAW` with the **same `id`** as the registry entry (summary, bullets, requirements, dos, donts, article).
4. **Remove a feature** тАФ remove from registry, sidebar links, and content; orphaned entries throw `DocumentationSyncError` on import.
5. Run `npm run docs:validate` before finishing.

## Do not

- Hard-code nav hrefs/labels in `dashboard-nav.tsx` or `admin-nav.tsx` without updating the registry.
- Duplicate route strings in guide `location` fields when the registry already defines them тАФ locations are auto-applied from the registry unless `quickReference.location` overrides.
- Skip guide updates when adding admin-only or customer-facing screens.

## Guide surfaces in the app

- Customer: `/how-it-works?tab=user-guide`, dashboard header **Documentation**
- Admin: `/admin/guide` (admin layout only)
